  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: 1.10.18\r\nOS & Version: Linux Ubuntu 20.04\r\nCommit hash : \"Geth/v1.10.18-stable-de23cf91/linux-amd64/go1.18.1\"\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\ngraphql endpoint should be queryable using specified http.vhosts like for RPC\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n\"invalid host specified\"\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\nFirst node : --graphql --http --http.addr 'A.B.C.D' --http.vhosts 'geth.ethereum-mainnet.ovh.int.kaiko.com,geth00.ethereum-mainnet.ovh.int.kaiko.com'\r\nSecond node : --graphql --http --http.addr 'A.B.C.D' --http.vhosts 'geth.ethereum-mainnet.ovh.int.kaiko.com,geth01.ethereum-mainnet.ovh.int.kaiko.com'\r\n\r\nBoth nodes in DNS RR geth.ethereum-mainnet.ovh.int.kaiko.com\r\n\r\n```\r\ncurl -X POST http://geth.ethereum-mainnet.ovh.int.kaiko.com:8545/graphql -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" --data '{ \"query\": \"query txInfo { block(number:13870512) { hash number difficulty logsBloom nonce parent { hash } timestamp transactions { createdContract { address } cumulativeGasUsed from { address } gasUsed logs { account { address } data index topics } hash index to { address } status } number } }\" }' \r\n```\r\n\r\nWorkaround, by specifying hostname as 'localhost' :\r\n\r\n```\r\ncurl -X POST http://geth.ethereum-mainnet.ovh.int.kaiko.com:8545/graphql -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" --data '{ \"query\": \"query txInfo { block(number:13870512) { hash number difficulty logsBloom nonce parent { hash } timestamp transactions { createdContract { address } cumulativeGasUsed from { address } gasUsed logs { account { address } data index topics } hash index to { address } status } number } }\" }' -H \"Host: localhost\"\r\n```\r\n",
